definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(P)+ + L-arginine -eq- nicotinamide + N2-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + NAD+ -eq- NADP+ + NADH + H+, driving the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other. In the course of the reaction (left to right) one H atom is transferred from inside the cell to outside. The reaction is B-specific (i.e. the pro-S hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to both NAD+ and NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + n oxidized hemoprotein -eq- NADP+ + n reduced hemoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + quinone acceptor -eq- NADP+ + hydroquinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + quinone -eq- NADP+ + semiquinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-acetyl-L-homoserine + methanethiol -eq- L-methionine + acetate. Also reacts with other thiols and H2S, producing homocysteine or thioethers.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-succinyl-L-homoserine + L-cysteine -eq- cystathionine + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + RNA 3'-terminal-phosphate -eq- AMP + diphosphate + RNA terminal-2',3'-cyclic-phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + DNA(n+1). Catalyzes RNA-template-directed extension of the 3'- end of a DNA strand by one deoxynucleotide at a time.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + RNA(n+1) -  uses an RNA template.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + ribonucleotide(n) + ribonucleotide(m) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + ribonucleotide(n+m).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-2-hydroxy-acid + O2 -eq- 2-oxo acid + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + dolichyl phosphate -eq- UMP + N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-diphosphodolichol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + lysosomal-enzyme D-mannose -eq- UMP + lysosomal-enzyme N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-phospho-D-mannose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate + UTP -eq- diphosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose -eq- UDP-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + 2 NAD(+) + UDP-alpha-D-glucose -eq- 3 H(+) + 2 NADH + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate.
Catalysis of the addition of UDP-glucose on to asparagine-linked (N-linked) oligosaccharides of the form Man7-9GlcNAc2 on incorrectly folded glycoproteins.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate + UTP -eq- diphosphate + UDP-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 pyruvate -eq- 2-acetolactate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 acetyl-CoA -eq- CoA + acetoacetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- acetate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + acetate + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + acetyl-CoA -eq- CoA + 3-oxoacyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + acetyl-CoA + HCO3- -eq- ADP + phosphate + malonyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetylcholine + H2O -eq- choline + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + N-acetyl-L-glutamate -eq- ADP + N-acetyl-L-glutamate-5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + N(2)-acetyl-L-ornithine -eq- N-acetyl-L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an orthophosphoric monoester + H2O -eq- an alcohol + phosphate, with an acid pH optimum.

Catalysis of the reaction -  citrate -eq- isocitrate. The reaction occurs in two steps -  (1) citrate -eq- cis-aconitate + H2O, (2) cis-aconitate + H2O -eq- isocitrate. This reaction is the interconversion of citrate and isocitrate via the labile, enzyme-bound intermediate cis-aconitate. Water is removed from one part of the citrate molecule and added back to a different atom to form isocitrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + acceptor -eq- 2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a long-chain carboxylic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + an acyl-CoA -  long-chain fatty acids have chain lengths of C13 to C22.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + O2 -eq- trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an acyl phosphate + H2O -eq- a carboxylate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + diphosphate -eq- adenine + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosine + H2O -eq- inosine + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + adenosine -eq- ADP + AMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction drives the unwinding of the DNA helix.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction drives the unwinding of an RNA helix.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + Cu2+(in) --gt- ADP + phosphate + Cu2+(out).
Catalysis of the movement of phospholipids from one membrane bilayer leaflet to the other, driven by the hydrolysis of ATP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H2O -eq- adenosine + L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + H(+) -eq- S-adenosylmethioninamine + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  8-amino-7-oxononanoate + S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) -eq- 7,8-diaminononanoate + S-adenosyl-4-methylthio-2-oxobutanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP -eq- 3',5'-cyclic AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + AMP -eq- 2 ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N6-(1,2-dicarboxyethyl)AMP -eq- fumarate + AMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-aspartate + GTP + IMP -eq- N(6)-(1,2-dicarboxyethyl)-AMP + GDP + 3 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + adenylylsulfate -eq- ADP + 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate.
